ers.”\n\nEach police department is competing to see who can be the top fund-raisers in the state.\n\nTo donate to ACPD’s team clickhere.To donate to CPD’s team clickhere.\n\nDo you have a story idea? Send us your news tiphere.\n\nCopyright 2024 WVIR. All rights reserved.", "title": "Charlottesville and Albemarle police participate in Special Olympic Torch Run", "top-image": "https://gray-wvir-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/TJMMTRDM7VCELBP4ZBZMYSTHOM.png?auth=9bed19ae864066428dfd4c5717b1c01aa65275cd52db04352b3e66fc1aa35737&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "domain": "www.29news.com", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "Each year law enforcement torch run members carry the “Flame of Hope” throughout the commonwealth to raise funds and awareness for Special Olympics Virginia athletes.", "keywords": "WVIR,29News,Charlottesville Police Department,Albemarle County Police Department,ACPD,CPD,Special Olympics,Virginia Special Olympics,central Virginia"}